        "content": "<p>Is there a simple way of using <code>well_ordering_rel</code> for sorting a <code>finset</code>?<br>\nE.g. when trying ...</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">data.finset</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">set_theory.ordinal</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">example</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">finset</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">list</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">f.sort</span> <span class=\"n\">well_ordering_rel</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>... there are missing instances:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">failed</span> <span class=\"n\">to</span> <span class=\"n\">synthesize</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span> <span class=\"kd\">class</span> <span class=\"kd\">instance</span> <span class=\"n\">for</span>\n<span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"bp\">?</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">finset</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span> <span class=\"n\">decidable_rel</span> <span class=\"n\">well_ordering_rel</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">failed</span> <span class=\"n\">to</span> <span class=\"n\">synthesize</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span> <span class=\"kd\">class</span> <span class=\"kd\">instance</span> <span class=\"n\">for</span>\n<span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"bp\">?</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">finset</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span> <span class=\"n\">is_antisymm</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"n\">well_ordering_rel</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">failed</span> <span class=\"n\">to</span> <span class=\"n\">synthesize</span> <span class=\"n\">type</span> <span class=\"kd\">class</span> <span class=\"kd\">instance</span> <span class=\"n\">for</span>\n<span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"bp\">?</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n<span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">finset</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span> <span class=\"n\">is_total</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"n\">well_ordering_rel</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is it possible to prove that <code>well_ordering_rel</code> is antisymm?</p>",
